    Paralysis stalks forward, his pstol poised to fire on any moving object. 
Aracnia, like a true Predacon Commander, stays behinde and manages from the 
cover.
    "Do you see it?" She demanded, tired of walking. The journey was long 
enough, and now they couldnt find the new bot.
    Paralysis shrugged. He didnt see anything. Walking around the clearing he 
made sure no one else was around.
    Then, Black Aracnia stumbled apon the empty stasis pod, and the tracks of 
the Allience members who stole the warrior. "What?! What?! No! No! No!"
    Her fit of rage cause the birds to scatter, and a few deer to gallop 
away. She stomped the ground and, basically, threw a tantrum.
    "Ah, Commander. Im sure that the bot wasnt worth it anyways." Paralysis 
said, unknowing it would direct her rage towrds him.
    "Shut up wart face! Lets just go home! Those damn Allience Members! Who 
do they think they are? The Beast Wars peace keepers or something? Argh! 
Return to base, now!" She screamed.
